OutBoundIamPolicy:
  Type: AWS::IAM::Policy
  Properties:
    PolicyName: !Sub ${AppName}-outbound-policy-${EnvironGroup}
    Roles:
      - !Ref OutBoundIamRole
    PolicyDocument:
      Version: '2012-10-17'
      Statement:
        # Existing SNS publish permissions
        - Action:
            - sns:Publish
          Effect: Allow
          Resource:
            - !Sub arn:${AWS::Partition}:sns:${AWS::Region}:${AWS::AccountId}:${AppName}-outbound-topic-${EnvironGroup}.fifo

        # ✅ Add permission for EventBridge PutEvents
        - Action:
            - events:PutEvents
          Effect: Allow
          Resource:
            - !Sub arn:${AWS::Partition}:events:${AWS::Region}:${AWS::AccountId}:event-bus/${EventBusName}
Replace ${EventBusName} with your actual bus logical name or parameter (e.g. ${AppName}-event-bus-${EnvironGroup}).

The !Sub syntax automatically substitutes CloudFormation pseudo parameters like:

${AWS::Partition} → aws

${AWS::Region} → e.g. us-east-1

${AWS::AccountId} → your AWS account ID

arn:aws:events:us-east-1:123456789012:event-bus/myApp-event-bus-qa

